 February 12,  2015Orange County RegisterTeaching cyber savvyBy Lauren Williams
Just as schools are learning to use social media to reach students, students are learning to use social media in their academic lives, not just their social lives. That's especially true when it comes to what is and is not appropriate to share.

“I think that message of ‘Facebook is forever' and ‘authorities are looking at it' has come through. It is no longer a safe space for peer sharing,” said Mimi Ito, a cultural anthropologist at UC Irvine who specializes in how young people use social media in the U.S. and Japan.







Read the full story on the 
Orange County Register
website.



 
 
 

